genGroupVersion.name: genGroupVersion
genGroupVersion.description: The version for the general group.

genProductName.name: genProductName
genProductName.description: A textual description of the device.

genProductNumber.name: genProductNumber
genProductNumber.description: The product number of the device.

genSerialNumber.name: genSerialNumber
genSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the device.

genCableType.name: genCableType
genCableType.description: Indicates the network cable type connected to the device.

genVersion.name: genVersion
genVersion.description: A string indicating the version of the firmware.

genConfigurationDirty.name: genConfigurationDirty
genConfigurationDirty.description: A variable's value has been changed which will require that the device be reset or power cycled before it will take effect. Set cmdReset to take this action. A list of critical variables that will cause genConfigurationDirty to be set follows: snmpGetCommunityName, snmpSetCommunityName, trPriority, trEarlyTokenRelease, trPacketSize, trRouting, trLocallyAdminAddr, psJetAdminEnabled, outputType, outputHandshake, tcpipEnabled, tcpipIPAddress, tcpipDefaultGateway, tcpipSubnetMask, tcpipUsingNetProtocols, tcpipBootProtocolsEnabled, tcpipRawPortNumber, tcpipMLPTCPPort, tcpipMLPPort, nwEnabled, nwSetFrameFormat, nwMode, nwPrintServerName, nwPrintServerPassword, nwQueueScanTime, nwFileServerName, nwPortPrinterNumber, nwPortFontDownload, nwPortPCLQueue, nwPortPSQueue, nwPortFormsOn, nwPortNotification, bvEnabled, bvSetSequencedRouting, bvLoginName, bvLoginPassword, bvPrintServiceName, bvPrintServiceRouting, lmEnabled, eTalkEnabled

genCompanyName.name: genCompanyName
genCompanyName.description: A string indicating the manufacturer of the device.

genCompanyLoc.name: genCompanyLoc
genCompanyLoc.description: A string indicating the location of the manufacturer of the device.

genCompanyPhone.name: genCompanyPhone
genCompanyPhone.description: A string indicating the phone number of the manufacturer of the device.

genCompanyTechSupport.name: genCompanyTechSupport
genCompanyTechSupport.description: A string indicating the technical support information for the device.

genNumProtocols.name: genNumProtocols
genNumProtocols.description: The number of network protocols supported on the device.

genProtocolTable.name: genProtocolTable
genProtocolTable.description: A list of network protocols. The number of entries is given by the value of genNumProtocols.

genProtocolEntry.name: genProtocolEntry
genProtocolEntry.description: A network protocol supported on the device.

genProtocolIndex.name: genProtocolIndex
genProtocolIndex.description: A unique value for each network protocol. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of genNumProtocols. The value for each protocol must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

genProtocolDescr.name: genProtocolDescr
genProtocolDescr.description: A textual string describing the network protocol.

genProtocolID.name: genProtocolID
genProtocolID.description: A unique identification number for the network protocol.

genSysUpTimeString.name: genSysUpTimeString
genSysUpTimeString.description: A string indicating the system up time for the device.

cmdGroupVersion.name: cmdGroupVersion
cmdGroupVersion.description: The version for the commands group.

cmdReset.name: cmdReset
cmdReset.description: A value of 2 will reset the device. The following list of variables will also cause the device to reset itself. cmdRestoreDefaults, snmpRestoreDefaults, trRestoreDefaults, outputRestoreDefaults, tcpipRestoreDefaults, tcpipFirmwareUpgrade, nwRestoreDefaults, nwFirmwareUpgrade, bvRestoreDefaults, bvFirmwareUpgrade, eTalkRestoreDefaults

cmdPrintConfig.name: cmdPrintConfig
cmdPrintConfig.description: A value of 2 will cause the device to print a configuration page.

cmdRestoreDefaults.name: cmdRestoreDefaults
cmdRestoreDefaults.description: A value of 2 will restore all parameters on the device to factory defaults, as well as reset the device.

snmpGroupVersion.name: snmpGroupVersion
snmpGroupVersion.description: The version for the snmp group.

snmpRestoreDefaults.name: snmpRestoreDefaults
snmpRestoreDefaults.description: A value of 2 will restore all SNMP parameters on the device to factory defaults, as well as reset the device.

snmpGetCommunityName.name: snmpGetCommunityName
snmpGetCommunityName.description: Get community name for the managed node. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

snmpSetCommunityName.name: snmpSetCommunityName
snmpSetCommunityName.description: Set community name for the managed node. This value cannot be read, just set. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

snmpTrapCommunityName.name: snmpTrapCommunityName
snmpTrapCommunityName.description: Trap community name for the managed node.

driverGroupVersion.name: driverGroupVersion
driverGroupVersion.description: The version for the driver group.

driverRXPacketsUnavailable.name: driverRXPacketsUnavailable
driverRXPacketsUnavailable.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol due to a lack of buffer space.

driverRXPacketErrors.name: driverRXPacketErrors
driverRXPacketErrors.description: The number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

driverTXPacketErrors.name: driverTXPacketErrors
driverTXPacketErrors.description: The number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors.

driverChecksumErrors.name: driverChecksumErrors
driverChecksumErrors.description: The number of packets containing checksum errors received.

trGroupVersion.name: trGroupVersion
trGroupVersion.description: The version for the tokenRing group.

trRestoreDefaults.name: trRestoreDefaults
trRestoreDefaults.description: A value of 2 will restore all token-ring parameters on the device to factory defaults, as well as reset the device.

trPriority.name: trPriority
trPriority.description: The token which is passed around the ring until a station needs it can be assigned a priority from 0 to 6. Priority 0 is the lowest and 6 is the highest. The priority of the device can be increased to improve performance. However, the performance of file servers and crucial stations could be affected. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the device must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

trEarlyTokenRelease.name: trEarlyTokenRelease
trEarlyTokenRelease.description: Early token release allows the device to release the token immediately after transmitting data but only on 16 Mbps systems. This feature enhances ring performance. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the device must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

trPacketSize.name: trPacketSize
trPacketSize.description: You should only change the packet size if you are using a driver for your Token Ring adapter which allows packet sizes greater than One_K. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the device must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

trRouting.name: trRouting
trRouting.description: Set this variable to change the source routing configuration on the device. Off: No source routing. All, None: All-routes broadcast, nonbroadcast return. The frame will be transmitted on every route within the network resulting in multiple copies on a given ring. Single, All: Single-route broadcast, all routes broadcast return. The frame will be transmitted across the designated bridges, which will result in the frame appearing only once on each ring. The response frame is on all routes broadcast to the originator. Single, None: Single-route broadcast, nonbroadcast return. The frame will be transmitted across designated bridges, which will result in the frame appearing only once each ring. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the device must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

trLocallyAdminAddr.name: trLocallyAdminAddr
trLocallyAdminAddr.description: This is the locally administered node address for the device. Valid values are 000000000000 and between 400000000000 and 7FFFFFFFFFFF. A value of 000000000000 indicates that a locally administered address is not in use.

psGroupVersion.name: psGroupVersion
psGroupVersion.description: The version for the psGeneral group.

psJetAdminEnabled.name: psJetAdminEnabled
psJetAdminEnabled.description: Indicates whether or not the JetAdmin support is enabled on the print server. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

psVerifyConfiguration.name: psVerifyConfiguration
psVerifyConfiguration.description: This variable is used to force the print server to verify valid configuration settings. Setting the variable to the appropriate enumeration will cause the print server to verify the settings for that enumeration. If the settings are valid, the result of the set will be OK. If the settings are not valid, the result will be BadValue. Gets on this variable will always return 0. 1 - Indicates whether or not the current serial configuration is valid. Valid configurations - If the serial port is set in bidirectional mode, the baud rate must be less than 115200 and the handshaking must be set to hardware handshaking. 2 - Not used yet.

outputGroupVersion.name: outputGroupVersion
outputGroupVersion.description: The version for the output group.

outputRestoreDefaults.name: outputRestoreDefaults
outputRestoreDefaults.description: A value of 2 will restore all output parameters on the print server to factory defaults, as well as reset the print server.

outputCommandsTable.name: outputCommandsTable
outputCommandsTable.description: A list of physical output ports. The number of entries is given by the value of outputNumPorts.

outputCommandsEntry.name: outputCommandsEntry
outputCommandsEntry.description: A physical output port on the print server.

outputCancelCurrentJob.name: outputCancelCurrentJob
outputCancelCurrentJob.description: A value of 2 will cancel the job currently printing on that port.

outputNumPorts.name: outputNumPorts
outputNumPorts.description: The number of physical output ports on the print server.

outputTable.name: outputTable
outputTable.description: A list of physical output ports. The number of entries is given by the value of outputNumPorts.

outputEntry.name: outputEntry
outputEntry.description: A physical output port on the print server.

outputIndex.name: outputIndex
outputIndex.description: A unique value for each physical output port. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of outputNumPorts. The value for each protocol must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

outputName.name: outputName
outputName.description: A textual description of the output port.

outputStatusString.name: outputStatusString
outputStatusString.description: A string indicating the status of the physical output port.

outputStatus.name: outputStatus
outputStatus.description: Indicates status of the printer. Get outputExtendedStatus for further information.

outputExtendedStatus.name: outputExtendedStatus
outputExtendedStatus.description: Indicates printer status to be used in conjunction with outputStatus.

outputPrinter.name: outputPrinter
outputPrinter.description: The type of printer the output port is attached to. Even if the group is supported, this variable may not be supported.

outputLanguageSwitching.name: outputLanguageSwitching
outputLanguageSwitching.description: Indicates the language switching option for the physical port. Even if the group is supported, this variable may not be supported.

outputConfigLanguage.name: outputConfigLanguage
outputConfigLanguage.description: Indicates the language that configuration pages will be printed in. If set to off, a config sheet will not be printed on this port.

outputPCLString.name: outputPCLString
outputPCLString.description: This string will be sent out the physical port if (1) outputLanguageSwitching is set to PCL or outputLanguageSwitching is set to Auto and the job is determined to be PCL, and (2) outputPrinter is set to No_Specific_Printer. Even if the group is supported, this variable may not be supported.

outputPSString.name: outputPSString
outputPSString.description: This string will be sent out the physical port if (1) outputLanguageSwitching is set to PostScript or outputLanguageSwitching is set to Auto and the job is determined to be PostScript, and (2) outputPrinter is set to No_Specific_Printer. Even if the group is supported, this variable may not be supported.

outputCascaded.name: outputCascaded
outputCascaded.description: A value of 2 indicates that the physical output port is connected to an Extended System's printer sharing device. Even if the group is supported, this variable may not be supported.

outputSetting.name: outputSetting
outputSetting.description: Indicates the type (and optionally speed) for the physical output port. Setting this variable to physical connections (such as Parallel) will result in an error. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

outputOwner.name: outputOwner
outputOwner.description: Indicates which protocol or task currently is printing on the port.

outputBIDIStatusEnabled.name: outputBIDIStatusEnabled
outputBIDIStatusEnabled.description: A value of 2 indicates that the BIDI status system is enabled.

outputPrinterModel.name: outputPrinterModel
outputPrinterModel.description: A string indicating the printer model attached to the output port.

outputPrinterDisplay.name: outputPrinterDisplay
outputPrinterDisplay.description: A string indicating the message on the attached printer front panel.

outputCapabilities.name: outputCapabilities
outputCapabilities.description: This field is implemented as a BIT mask. If the bit is set then the port is capable of functioning in this mode. Bit Property --- ------------------------ 0 Serial Unidirectional Baud 9600 1 Serial Unidirectional Baud 19200 2 Serial Unidirectional Baud 38400 3 Serial Unidirectional Baud 57600 4 Serial Unidirectional Baud 115200 5 Serial Bidirectional Baud 9600 6 Serial Bidirectional Baud 19200 7 Serial Bidirectional Baud 38400 8 Serial Bidirectional Baud 57600 19 Infrared Input on serial port 20 Serial Input 21 Serial Configuration Settings 22 Parallel Compatibility Mode (no bidi) 23 IEEE 1284 Standard Nibble Mode 24 ZLink 25 Bidirectional Support (PJL status) 26 Serial Software Handshaking 27 Serial Output 28 Extended Link Technology 29 Printer Internal (MIO) 30 IEEE 1284 ECP or Fast Nibble Mode

outputHandshake.name: outputHandshake
outputHandshake.description: If the port in serial mode operation this indicates the handshaking method being used. Setting this value to 'not- supported' will result in an error. Setting this value on non serial capable ports will result in an error. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

outputDataBits.name: outputDataBits
outputDataBits.description: If the port in serial mode operation this indicates the number of data bits being used. Setting this value to 'not- supported' will result in an error. Setting this value on non serial capable ports will result in an error. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

outputStopBits.name: outputStopBits
outputStopBits.description: If the port in serial mode operation this indicates the number of stop bits being used. Setting this value to 'not- supported' will result in an error. Setting this value on non serial capable ports will result in an error. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

outputParity.name: outputParity
outputParity.description: If the port in serial mode operation this indicates the parity checking method being used. Setting this value to 'not- supported' will result in an error. Setting this value on non serial capable ports will result in an error. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

outputBaudRate.name: outputBaudRate
outputBaudRate.description: If the port in serial mode operation this indicates the baud rate being used. Setting this value on non serial capable ports will result in an error. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

outputProtocolManager.name: outputProtocolManager
outputProtocolManager.description: Indicates the type of output protocol manager being used on the port. Protocol-none means either there is no printer attached or the print server has not yet determined which output managers are supported on the printer. Protocol-compatibility means the printer does not support any of the protocol managers supported by the print server. Protocol-1284-4 means the output is using the 1284.4 logical port protocol manager.

outputDisplayMask.name: outputDisplayMask
outputDisplayMask.description: Bit mask describing what should be displayed by the utilities bit Description --- ----------- 0 outputCancelCurrentJob (Includes all CancelCurrentJob info) 1 outputName 2 outputStatusString 3 outputStatus 4 outputExtendedStatus 5 outputPrinter 6 outputLanguageSwitching 7 outputConfigLanguage 8 outputString (Includes outputPCLString and outputPSString) 9 outputCascaded 10 outputSetting 11 outputOwner 12 outputBIDIStatusEnabled 13 outputPrinterModel 14 outputPrinterDisplay 15 outputHandshake 16 outputJobLog (includes all job logging) 17 outputSerialConfig

outputAvailableTrapsMask.name: outputAvailableTrapsMask
outputAvailableTrapsMask.description: Bit mask describing what output printer traps are available bit Description --- ----------- 0 online 1 offline 2 printer attached 3 toner low 4 paper out 5 paper jam 6 door open 7 printer error

outputNumLogEntries.name: outputNumLogEntries
outputNumLogEntries.description: The number of job log entries per output port.

outputJobLogTable.name: outputJobLogTable
outputJobLogTable.description: A 2 dimensional list of Job log entries indexed by the output port number and the log entry index (1 through outputNumJobLogEntries). The number of entries per output port is given by the value of outputNumJobLogEntries.

outputJobLogInformation.name: outputJobLogInformation
outputJobLogInformation.description: A textual description of print job information. The protocol, source, and file size are always included. Other information such as File Server, Queue, File Name, etc will be included if available.

outputJobLogTime.name: outputJobLogTime
outputJobLogTime.description: A string indicating the elasped time since the last job was printed. Reported in form X hours X minutes X seconds.

outputTotalJobTable.name: outputTotalJobTable
outputTotalJobTable.description: Table showing the total number of jobs printed for each port.

outputTotalJobIndex.name: outputTotalJobIndex
outputTotalJobIndex.description: A unique value for entry in the outputTotalJobTable. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of numPorts.

outputTotalJobsLogged.name: outputTotalJobsLogged
outputTotalJobsLogged.description: The total number of jobs printed by the port since the print server was powered on.

tcpipGroupVersion.name: tcpipGroupVersion
tcpipGroupVersion.description: The version for the tcpip group.

tcpipEnabled.name: tcpipEnabled
tcpipEnabled.description: Indicates whether or not the tcpip protocol stack is enabled on the print server. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

tcpipRestoreDefaults.name: tcpipRestoreDefaults
tcpipRestoreDefaults.description: A value of 2 will restore all tcpip parameters on the print server to factory defaults, as well as reset the print server.

tcpipFirmwareUpgrade.name: tcpipFirmwareUpgrade
tcpipFirmwareUpgrade.description: A value of 2 will put the print server into firmware upgrade mode waiting to receive a firmware upgrade file via tftp.

tcpipIPAddress.name: tcpipIPAddress
tcpipIPAddress.description: The Internet Address. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

tcpipDefaultGateway.name: tcpipDefaultGateway
tcpipDefaultGateway.description: The default gateway for the print server. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

tcpipSubnetMask.name: tcpipSubnetMask
tcpipSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask for the print server. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

tcpipUsingNetProtocols.name: tcpipUsingNetProtocols
tcpipUsingNetProtocols.description: A value of 2 indicates that the print server is using a combination of RARP, BOOTP, default IP address, or gleaning to determine its IP address. See tcpipBootProtocolsEnabled to determine which boot protocols are enabled. If the value of tcpipUsingNetProtocols is 1, the IP address is stored permanently in flash memory. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

tcpipBootProtocolsEnabled.name: tcpipBootProtocolsEnabled
tcpipBootProtocolsEnabled.description: This is the 16 bit mask which determines which boot protocols will be used to determine the print server's IP address. BIT Boot Protocol Enabled --- -------------------------- 0 RARP 1 BootP 2 DHCP 3 Gleaning 4 Default Address Enabled (If no address after 2 minutes timeout and go to 198.102.102.254) A value of 31 indicates that all boot protocols are enabled. These protocols will only be used if tcpipUsingNetProtocols is set to 2. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

tcpipIPAddressSource.name: tcpipIPAddressSource
tcpipIPAddressSource.description: This variable indicates how the IP address for the print server was determined.

tcpipIPAddressServerAddress.name: tcpipIPAddressServerAddress
tcpipIPAddressServerAddress.description: This variable indicates the source of the IP address if a boot protocol was used. This value will be 0.0.0.0 if no boot server was used.

tcpipTimeoutChecking.name: tcpipTimeoutChecking
tcpipTimeoutChecking.description: A value of 2 indicates that a packet timeout will be active on all tcp connections. If a packet has not been received from the connection within this timeout the connection will be reset. To set this timeout, see tcpipTimeoutCheckingValue

tcpipNumTraps.name: tcpipNumTraps
tcpipNumTraps.description: The number of UDP trap destinations.

tcpipTrapTable.name: tcpipTrapTable
tcpipTrapTable.description: A list of UDP trap definitions. The number of entries is given by the value of tcpipNumTraps.

tcpipTrapIndex.name: tcpipTrapIndex
tcpipTrapIndex.description: A unique value for entry in the tcpipTrapTable. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of tcpipNumTraps.

tcpipTrapDestination.name: tcpipTrapDestination
tcpipTrapDestination.description: This is the IP address that traps are sent to. A value of 0.0.0.0 will disable traps over UDP.

tcpipProtocolTrapMask.name: tcpipProtocolTrapMask
tcpipProtocolTrapMask.description: This is the 16 bit mask which determines which protocol specific traps will be sent out via UDP. Currently no protocol specific traps are supported.

tcpipPrinterTrapMask.name: tcpipPrinterTrapMask
tcpipPrinterTrapMask.description: This is the 16 bit mask which determines which printer specific traps will be sent out via UDP. A value of 65535 indicates that all printer specific traps should be reported via UDP. BIT CONDITION --- -------------------------- 0 On-line (Condition cleared) 1 Off-line 2 No printer attached 3 Toner Low 4 Paper Out 5 Paper Jam 6 Door Open 15 Printer Error

tcpipOutputTrapMask.name: tcpipOutputTrapMask
tcpipOutputTrapMask.description: This is the 16 bit mask which determines which physical output ports will be checked when generating printer specific traps to be sent out via UDP. A value of 65535 indicates that all physical output ports will generate traps. BIT CONDITION --- -------------------------- 0 Port 1 1 Port 2 2 Port 3 3 Port 4 ... ...

tcpipBanners.name: tcpipBanners
tcpipBanners.description: A value of 2 indicates that banners will be printed with tcpip jobs. Even if the group is supported, this variable may not be supported.

tcpipWinsAddress.name: tcpipWinsAddress
tcpipWinsAddress.description: The IP address of the WINS server. The print server will register its sysName to this WINS server.

tcpipWinsAddressSource.name: tcpipWinsAddressSource
tcpipWinsAddressSource.description: The source of the WINS server address. If set to dhcp, the print server will use the WINS address supplied with dhcp. If it is set to permanent, it will use the WINS address stored in flash.

tcpipConfigPassword.name: tcpipConfigPassword
tcpipConfigPassword.description: The print server html/telnet configuration password. This value cannot be read, just set.

tcpipTimeoutCheckingValue.name: tcpipTimeoutCheckingValue
tcpipTimeoutCheckingValue.description: The TCP connection timeout in seconds. A value of 0 has the same effect as disabling timeout checking.

tcpipArpInterval.name: tcpipArpInterval
tcpipArpInterval.description: The ARP interval in minutes. The print server will ARP itself once when this timer expires. Set to 0 to disable.

tcpipRawPortNumber.name: tcpipRawPortNumber
tcpipRawPortNumber.description: The raw TCP port number the print server will listen for print jobs on. On multiple port devices, additional ports will sequentially follow this port number. The default port is 9100. Setting this value to a TCP port that is in use by another TCP application will return an error. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

tcpipNumSecurity.name: tcpipNumSecurity
tcpipNumSecurity.description: The number of secure IP address ranges.

tcpipSecurityTable.name: tcpipSecurityTable
tcpipSecurityTable.description: A list of secure IP address ranges. This adds security for both printing and admin rights. AdminEnabled: When the admin enabled field is set to yes for a secure address range, the print server may only be configured via IP from IP address within that range. If the admin field is not set for any address ranges, the print server will accept admin commands from any IP address which has the valid community names and/or passwords. PortMask: When there is a port mask set for a secure IP address range, the print server will only accept TCP/IP print jobs from hosts that are in the secure address range. If there are no ranges with a port mask set, the print server will accept TCP/IP print jobs from any host. The number of entries is given by the value of tcpipNumSecurity.

tcpipSecurityIndex.name: tcpipSecurityIndex
tcpipSecurityIndex.description: A unique value for entry in the tcpipSecurityTable. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of tcpipNumSecurity.

tcpipSecureStartIPAddress.name: tcpipSecureStartIPAddress
tcpipSecureStartIPAddress.description: This is the starting IP address for the secure IP address range. A value of 0.0.0.0 for both tcpipStartIPAddress and tcpipEndIPAddress will disable the address range.

tcpipSecureEndIPAddress.name: tcpipSecureEndIPAddress
tcpipSecureEndIPAddress.description: This is the ending IP address for the secure IP address range. A value of 0.0.0.0 for both tcpipStartIPAddress and tcpipEndIPAddress will disable the address range.

tcpipSecurePrinterMask.name: tcpipSecurePrinterMask
tcpipSecurePrinterMask.description: This is the 8 bit mask which determines which physical output ports this range of IP addresses can print to. A value of 127 indicates that the range of IP addresses can print to any of the output ports. This value can not be configured until a valid start and end address range have been configured. BIT CONDITION --- -------------------------- 0 Port 1 1 Port 2 2 Port 3 3 Port 4 ... ... 8 Reserved, must be set to 0.

tcpipSecureAdminEnabled.name: tcpipSecureAdminEnabled
tcpipSecureAdminEnabled.description: This allows an advanced level of admin security for IP. Setting this will restrict which IP addresses can configure the print server. The correct community names and passwords are still required if this is used, it just adds another level of security. Indicates whether or not admin rights are enabled for this range of IP addresses. If no range of addresses has this enabled, then any IP address can configure the print server if it has the correct community names and/or passwords. If this field is set to yes for any range of addresses, the print server will only be configurable via IP from that range of addresses. This value can not be configured until a valid start and end address range have been configured.

tcpipLowBandwidth.name: tcpipLowBandwidth
tcpipLowBandwidth.description: A value of 2 will optimize the TCP stack for low bandwidth networks. A value of 1 will optimize the TCP stack for high bandwidth networks.

tcpipNumLogicalPrinters.name: tcpipNumLogicalPrinters
tcpipNumLogicalPrinters.description: The number of available logical printers.

tcpipMLPTable.name: tcpipMLPTable
tcpipMLPTable.description: A table of the available logical printers. The number of entries is given by the value of tcpipNumLogicalPrinters.

tcpipMLPIndex.name: tcpipMLPIndex
tcpipMLPIndex.description: A unique value for entry in the tcpipMLPTable. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of tcpipNumLogicalPrinters.

tcpipMLPName.name: tcpipMLPName
tcpipMLPName.description: Contains the name of the logical printer. This name is also the LPR remote queue name associated with the logical printer.

tcpipMLPPort.name: tcpipMLPPort
tcpipMLPPort.description: The number of the physical output port associated with the logical printer. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

tcpipMLPTCPPort.name: tcpipMLPTCPPort
tcpipMLPTCPPort.description: The TCP port associated with the logical printer. Any print data sent to this TCP port will be processed through this logical printer entry. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

tcpipMLPPreString.name: tcpipMLPPreString
tcpipMLPPreString.description: This contains any data that should be sent down to the printer at the beginning of jobs sent to this logical printer. To enter non-printable ascii characters in the string, enclose the decimal value inside of <>. For example, to enter an ESC-E the string would be '<27>E'.

tcpipMLPPostString.name: tcpipMLPPostString
tcpipMLPPostString.description: This contains any data that should be sent down to the printer at the end of jobs sent to this logical printer. To enter non-printable ascii characters in the string, enclose the decimal value inside of <>. For example, to enter an ESC-E the string would be '<27>E'.

tcpipMLPDeleteBytes.name: tcpipMLPDeleteBytes
tcpipMLPDeleteBytes.description: The number of bytes that will be deleted from the beginning of jobs sent to this logical printer.

tcpipSmtpServerAddr.name: tcpipSmtpServerAddr
tcpipSmtpServerAddr.description: The IP address of the e-mail server which will be used to send e-mail notification of printer status conditions. This address must contain the valid IP address of an e-mail server before any of the contents of the SmtpTable are used.

tcpipNumSmtpDestinations.name: tcpipNumSmtpDestinations
tcpipNumSmtpDestinations.description: The number of configurable e-mail destinations to receive printer status conditions.

tcpipSmtpTable.name: tcpipSmtpTable
tcpipSmtpTable.description: A list of SMTP e-mail addresses and printer status conditions to send e-mails for. The number of entries is given by the value of tcpipNumSmtpDestinations.

tcpipSmtpIndex.name: tcpipSmtpIndex
tcpipSmtpIndex.description: A unique value for entry in the tcpipSmtpTable. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of tcpipNumSmtpDestinations.

tcpipSmtpEmailAddr.name: tcpipSmtpEmailAddr
tcpipSmtpEmailAddr.description: This is the e-mail address that printer status conditions are sent to. If this string is empty the status conditions will not be sent.

tcpipSmtpProtocolMask.name: tcpipSmtpProtocolMask
tcpipSmtpProtocolMask.description: This is the 16 bit mask which determines which protocol specific conditions will be sent out via e-mail. Currently no protocol specific conditions are supported.

tcpipSmtpPrinterMask.name: tcpipSmtpPrinterMask
tcpipSmtpPrinterMask.description: This is the 16 bit mask which determines which printer specific conditions will be sent out via e-mail. A value of 65535 indicates that all printer specific conditions should be reported via e-mail. BIT CONDITION --- -------------------------- 0 On-line (Condition cleared) 1 Off-line 2 No printer attached 3 Toner Low 4 Paper Out 5 Paper Jam 6 Door Open 15 Printer Error

tcpipSmtpOutputMask.name: tcpipSmtpOutputMask
tcpipSmtpOutputMask.description: This is the 16 bit mask which determines which physical output ports will be checked when generating printer specific conditions to be sent out via e-mail. A value of 65535 indicates that all physical output ports will generate e-mails upon a change in status. BIT CONDITION --- -------------------------- 0 Port 1 1 Port 2 2 Port 3 3 Port 4 ... ...

tcpipWebAdminName.name: tcpipWebAdminName
tcpipWebAdminName.description: This is the admin name used by web configuration for login.

tcpipWebAdminPassword.name: tcpipWebAdminPassword
tcpipWebAdminPassword.description: This is the admin password used by web configuration for login.

tcpipWebUserName.name: tcpipWebUserName
tcpipWebUserName.description: This is the user name used by web configuration for login. Not currently used.

tcpipWebUserPassword.name: tcpipWebUserPassword
tcpipWebUserPassword.description: This is the user password used by web configuration for login. Not currently used.

tcpipWebHtttpPort.name: tcpipWebHtttpPort
tcpipWebHtttpPort.description: The port number used to communicate over http. Must be between 0 and 65535. It must not be the same as any other port used. Other ports used are 20, 21, 23, 515, & raw port numbers (9100, 9101, ... if at default)

tcpipWebFaqURL.name: tcpipWebFaqURL
tcpipWebFaqURL.description: This is the URL for FAQ at the ESI (or other OEM) website.

tcpipWebUpdateURL.name: tcpipWebUpdateURL
tcpipWebUpdateURL.description: This is the URL for finding firmware updates at the ESI (or other OEM) website.

tcpipWebCustomLinkName.name: tcpipWebCustomLinkName
tcpipWebCustomLinkName.description: This is the name assigned to the custom link defined by the user.

tcpipWebCustomLinkURL.name: tcpipWebCustomLinkURL
tcpipWebCustomLinkURL.description: This is the URL for a custom link specified by the user.

tcpipPOP3ServerAddress.name: tcpipPOP3ServerAddress
tcpipPOP3ServerAddress.description: The IP address of the POP3 server from which email will be retrieved. This address must contain the valid IP address of a POP3 server before any attempts to retrieve email will be made.

tcpipPOP3PollInterval.name: tcpipPOP3PollInterval
tcpipPOP3PollInterval.description: The number of seconds between attempts to retrieve mail from the POP3 server.

tcpipPOP3UserName.name: tcpipPOP3UserName
tcpipPOP3UserName.description: This is the user name for the print server's email account on the POP3 server.

tcpipPOP3Password.name: tcpipPOP3Password
tcpipPOP3Password.description: This is the password for the print server's email account on the POP3 server.

tcpipDomainName.name: tcpipDomainName
tcpipDomainName.description: This is the Domain name used by POP3 and SMTP.

tcpipError.name: tcpipError
tcpipError.description: Contains any tcpip specific error information.

tcpipDisplayMask.name: tcpipDisplayMask
tcpipDisplayMask.description: Bit mask describing what should be displayed by the utilities bit Description --- ----------- 0 tcpipAddress (Includes tcpipDefaultGateway and tcpipSubnetMask) 1 tcpipUsingNetProtocols (Includes tcpipBootProtocolsEnabled, tcpipAddressSource, tcpipAddressServerAddress) 2 tcpipTimeoutChecking 3 tcpipTraps (Includes all trap info) 4 tcpipBanners 5 tcpipSecurity (Includes all security info) 6 tcpipWinsAddress (Includes tcpipWinsAddressSource) 7 tcpipConfigPassword 8 tcpipTimeoutCheckingValue 9 tcpipArpInterval 10 tcpipRawPortNumber 11 tcpipError 12 tcpipLowBandwidth 13 tcpipMLP (Includes all logical printer settings)

nwGroupVersion.name: nwGroupVersion
nwGroupVersion.description: The version for the netware group.

nwEnabled.name: nwEnabled
nwEnabled.description: Indicates whether or not the NetWare protocol stack is enabled on the print server. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

nwRestoreDefaults.name: nwRestoreDefaults
nwRestoreDefaults.description: A value of 2 will restore all NetWare parameters on the print server to factory defaults, as well as reset the print server.

nwFirmwareUpgrade.name: nwFirmwareUpgrade
nwFirmwareUpgrade.description: A value of 2 will put the print server into firmware upgrade mode.

nwFrameFormat.name: nwFrameFormat
nwFrameFormat.description: Indicates the frame format that the print server is using. See nwSetFrameFormat to determine which frame frame format the print server is configured for.

nwSetFrameFormat.name: nwSetFrameFormat
nwSetFrameFormat.description: Indicates the frame format that the print server is using. Setting this value to 1 (Auto_Sense) indicates that automatic frame format sensing will be used. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

nwMode.name: nwMode
nwMode.description: Mode the print server is running in. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

nwPrintServerName.name: nwPrintServerName
nwPrintServerName.description: Contains print server name. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

nwPrintServerPassword.name: nwPrintServerPassword
nwPrintServerPassword.description: The print server password. This value cannot be read, just set. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

nwQueueScanTime.name: nwQueueScanTime
nwQueueScanTime.description: Determines how often, in tenths of a second that the print server will scan the queues for jobs. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

nwMaxFileServers.name: nwMaxFileServers
nwMaxFileServers.description: The print server maximum number of file servers which it can be attached to at once.

nwFileServerTable.name: nwFileServerTable
nwFileServerTable.description: A table of file servers to service.

nwFileServerEntry.name: nwFileServerEntry
nwFileServerEntry.description: A file server for the print server to service.

nwFileServerIndex.name: nwFileServerIndex
nwFileServerIndex.description: A unique value for each file server. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of nwMaxFileServers. The value for each server must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization. The first entry in the table is the default file server.

nwFileServerName.name: nwFileServerName
nwFileServerName.description: The file server name. This name will be NULL if there is no file server to be serviced. Only the default file server (the first entry in the table) can be set. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

nwFileServerConnectionStatus.name: nwFileServerConnectionStatus
nwFileServerConnectionStatus.description: The value describes the status of the connection between the file server and the print server.

nwPortTable.name: nwPortTable
nwPortTable.description: A table of NetWare port specific information.

nwPortEntry.name: nwPortEntry
nwPortEntry.description: An entry of NetWare port specific information.

nwPortIndex.name: nwPortIndex
nwPortIndex.description: A unique value for each physical output port. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of outputNumPorts. The value for each port must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

nwPortStatus.name: nwPortStatus
nwPortStatus.description: A string indicating the NetWare specific status of the physical output port.

nwPortPrinterNumber.name: nwPortPrinterNumber
nwPortPrinterNumber.description: Indicates the printer number for the print server to use when running in RPRinter mode. A value of 255 indicates that the port is unconfigured for RPRinter mode. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

nwPortFontDownload.name: nwPortFontDownload
nwPortFontDownload.description: This variable controls the font downloading feature of the print server. Disabled - Do not download fonts. Enabled, without Printer Sense - Only download fonts after the print server has been reset or power cycled. Enabled, with Printer Sense - Download fonts after the print server has been reset or power-cycled, or after the printer has been power-cycled. This option is only available on certain print servers. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

nwPortPCLQueue.name: nwPortPCLQueue
nwPortPCLQueue.description: A string indicating the name of the queue containing the PCL fonts to download when font downloading is enabled. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

nwPortPSQueue.name: nwPortPSQueue
nwPortPSQueue.description: A string indicating the name of the queue containing the PS fonts to download when font downloading is enabled. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

nwPortFormsOn.name: nwPortFormsOn
nwPortFormsOn.description: A value of 2 will enable forms checking. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

nwPortFormNumber.name: nwPortFormNumber
nwPortFormNumber.description: Indicates the form number to check jobs against when nwPortFormsOn is enabled.

nwPortNotification.name: nwPortNotification
nwPortNotification.description: A value of 2 will enable job notification.

nwNumTraps.name: nwNumTraps
nwNumTraps.description: The number of IPX trap destinations.

nwTrapTable.name: nwTrapTable
nwTrapTable.description: A list of IPX trap definitions. The number of entries is given by the value of nwNumTraps.

nwTrapIndex.name: nwTrapIndex
nwTrapIndex.description: A unique value for entry in the nwTrapTable. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of nwNumTraps.

nwTrapDestination.name: nwTrapDestination
nwTrapDestination.description: This is the network address that IPX traps are sent to. A value of 00 00 00 00 00 00 in conjunction with a nwTrapDestinationNet of 00 00 00 00 will disable traps over IPX.

nwTrapDestinationNet.name: nwTrapDestinationNet
nwTrapDestinationNet.description: This is the network number that IPX traps are sent to. A value of 00 00 00 00 in conjunction with a nwTrapDestination of 00 00 00 00 00 00 will disable traps over IPX.

nwProtocolTrapMask.name: nwProtocolTrapMask
nwProtocolTrapMask.description: This is the 16 bit mask which determines which protocol specific traps will be sent out via IPX. Currently no protocol specific traps are supported.

nwPrinterTrapMask.name: nwPrinterTrapMask
nwPrinterTrapMask.description: This is the 16 bit mask which determines which printer specific traps will be sent out via IPX. A value of 65535 indicates that all printer specific traps should be reported via IPX. BIT CONDITION --- -------------------------- 0 On-line (Condition cleared) 1 Off-line 2 No printer attached 3 Toner Low 4 Paper Out 5 Paper Jam 6 Door Open 15 Printer Error

nwOutputTrapMask.name: nwOutputTrapMask
nwOutputTrapMask.description: This is the 16 bit mask which determines which physical output ports will be checked when generating printer specific traps to be sent out via IPX. A value of 65535 indicates that all physical output ports will generate traps. BIT CONDITION --- -------------------------- 0 Port 1 1 Port 2 2 Port 3 3 Port 4 ... ...

nwNDSPrintServerName.name: nwNDSPrintServerName
nwNDSPrintServerName.description: Directory Services object used by the print server to connect to the NDS tree. This string contains the entire canonicalized name. NOTE: This variable must be stored in Unicode.

nwNDSPreferredDSTree.name: nwNDSPreferredDSTree
nwNDSPreferredDSTree.description: Directory Services tree to which the NDS print server initially connects.

nwNDSPreferredDSFileServer.name: nwNDSPreferredDSFileServer
nwNDSPreferredDSFileServer.description: The NetWare server to which the NDS print server initially makes a bindery connection.

nwNDSPacketCheckSumEnabled.name: nwNDSPacketCheckSumEnabled
nwNDSPacketCheckSumEnabled.description: Compute the checksum for packets. 1 = disabled 2 = enabled

nwNDSPacketSignatureLevel.name: nwNDSPacketSignatureLevel
nwNDSPacketSignatureLevel.description: Packet signature is a security method to prevent packet forging. 1 = disabled 2 = enabled 3 = preferred 4 = required

nwAvailablePrintModes.name: nwAvailablePrintModes
nwAvailablePrintModes.description: Reports which NetWare print modes are available. BIT CONDITION --- -------------------------- 0 PServer 1 RPrinter 2 NDS 3 SPX Direct 4 JetAdmin

nwDirectPrintEnabled.name: nwDirectPrintEnabled
nwDirectPrintEnabled.description: Indicates whether or not direct mode ipx/spx printing is enabled.

nwJAConfig.name: nwJAConfig
nwJAConfig.description: Indicates whether or not JetAdmin was used to configure the netware settings.

nwDisableSAP.name: nwDisableSAP
nwDisableSAP.description: Indicates whether or not SAPs are enabled.

nwError.name: nwError
nwError.description: Contains any NetWare specific error information.

nwDisplayMask.name: nwDisplayMask
nwDisplayMask.description: Bit mask describing what should be displayed by the utilities bit Description --- ----------- 0 nwFrameFormat 1 nwJetAdmin 2 nwFileServer (Includes all file server info) 3 nwMode 4 nwPrintServerName 5 nwPrintServerPassword 6 nwQueueScanTime 7 nwNetworkNumber 8 nwPortStatus 9 nwPortPrinterNumber 10 nwPortFontDownload (Includes nwPortPCLQueue and nwPortPSQueue) 11 nwPortFormsOn (Includes nwPortFormsNumber) 12 nwPortNotification 13 nwTraps (Includes all trap info) 14 nwNDSPrintServerName 15 nwNDSPreferredDSTree 16 nwNDSPreferredDSFileServer 17 nwNDSPacketCheckSumEnabled 18 nwNDSPacketSignatureLevel 19 nwDirectPrintEnabled 20 nwError 21 nwSapDisable

bvGroupVersion.name: bvGroupVersion
bvGroupVersion.description: The version for the vines group.

bvEnabled.name: bvEnabled
bvEnabled.description: Indicates whether or not the Banyan VINES protocol stack is enabled on the print server.

bvRestoreDefaults.name: bvRestoreDefaults
bvRestoreDefaults.description: A value of 2 will restore all VINES parameters on the print server to factory defaults, as well as reset the device.

bvFirmwareUpgrade.name: bvFirmwareUpgrade
bvFirmwareUpgrade.description: A value of 2 will put the print server into firmware upgrade mode.

bvSetSequenceRouting.name: bvSetSequenceRouting
bvSetSequenceRouting.description: Sets the VINES Routing selection. Automatic - Utilizes Sequenced Routing if available, otherwise uses Non-Sequenced Routing. Force-Sequenced - Will only use Sequenced Routing. Force-Non-Sequenced - Will only use Non-Sequenced Routing In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this. WARNING - Sequential Routing requires a VINES 5.5 or greater server on the same subnet.

bvDisableVPMan.name: bvDisableVPMan
bvDisableVPMan.description: A value of 2 will disable VPMan access to the print server for one minute.

bvLoginName.name: bvLoginName
bvLoginName.description: The StreetTalk name the device will use to login with. This value will be ESIxxxxxxxx where xxxxxxx is the Serial number of the device if it is unconfigured. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

bvLoginPassword.name: bvLoginPassword
bvLoginPassword.description: The password for the login name, bvLoginName. This value cannot be read, just set. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

bvNumberPrintServices.name: bvNumberPrintServices
bvNumberPrintServices.description: The number of Print Services this device supports.

bvPrintServiceTable.name: bvPrintServiceTable
bvPrintServiceTable.description: Table of Print Services for this device.

bvPrintServiceIndex.name: bvPrintServiceIndex
bvPrintServiceIndex.description: A unique value for each print service.

bvPrintServiceName.name: bvPrintServiceName
bvPrintServiceName.description: The StreetTalk Name for this Print Service. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

bvPrintServiceRouting.name: bvPrintServiceRouting
bvPrintServiceRouting.description: The output port that the print service will print to. This value will range from 0 to the number of output ports, see outputNumPorts. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

bvError.name: bvError
bvError.description: Contains any VINES specific error information.

bvRouting.name: bvRouting
bvRouting.description: The current VINES Routing being used by the device.

bvNumPrintServices.name: bvNumPrintServices
bvNumPrintServices.description: The number of Print Services this device supports.

bvPrintServiceStatusTable.name: bvPrintServiceStatusTable
bvPrintServiceStatusTable.description: Table of Print Service Status Entry's.

bvPSStatusIndex.name: bvPSStatusIndex
bvPSStatusIndex.description: A unique value for each status entry.

bvPSName.name: bvPSName
bvPSName.description: The StreetTalk Name for this Print Service.

bvPSDestination.name: bvPSDestination
bvPSDestination.description: Port Destination for this print service.

bvPrinterStatus.name: bvPrinterStatus
bvPrinterStatus.description: Printer status for this Print Service.

bvJobActive.name: bvJobActive
bvJobActive.description: Whether there is a VINES job active for this print service.

bvJobTitle.name: bvJobTitle
bvJobTitle.description: The title of the active print job.

bvJobSize.name: bvJobSize
bvJobSize.description: The size of the active print job.

bvJobNumber.name: bvJobNumber
bvJobNumber.description: The VINES job number of the active print job.

lmGroupVersion.name: lmGroupVersion
lmGroupVersion.description: The version for the lanManger group.

lmEnabled.name: lmEnabled
lmEnabled.description: Indicates whether or not the Lan Manager protocol stack is enabled on the print server. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

eTalkGroupVersion.name: eTalkGroupVersion
eTalkGroupVersion.description: The version for the eTalk group.

eTalkEnabled.name: eTalkEnabled
eTalkEnabled.description: Indicates whether or not the EtherTalk protocol stack is enabled on the print server. In order for changes to this variable to take effect, the print server must be reset. See cmdReset to do this.

eTalkRestoreDefaults.name: eTalkRestoreDefaults
eTalkRestoreDefaults.description: A value of 2 will restore all EtherTalk parameters on the print server to factory defaults, as well as reset the print server.

eTalkNetwork.name: eTalkNetwork
eTalkNetwork.description: Indicates the EtherTalk network number that the print server is currently using.

eTalkNode.name: eTalkNode
eTalkNode.description: Indicates the EtherTalk node number that the print server is currently using.

eTalkNumPorts.name: eTalkNumPorts
eTalkNumPorts.description: Indicates the number of physical output ports that are EtherTalk compatible.

eTalkPortTable.name: eTalkPortTable
eTalkPortTable.description: A table of EtherTalk specific port configuration information.

eTalkPortEntry.name: eTalkPortEntry
eTalkPortEntry.description: An entry of EtherTalk port specific information.

eTalkPortIndex.name: eTalkPortIndex
eTalkPortIndex.description: A unique value for each physical output port which is compatible with EtherTalk. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of eTalkNumPorts. The value for each port must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

eTalkPortEnable.name: eTalkPortEnable
eTalkPortEnable.description: Indicates whether or not the physical output port is enabled to print via EtherTalk and will show up in the Chooser.

eTalkName.name: eTalkName
eTalkName.description: This is the EtherTalk name for the print server.

eTalkActiveName.name: eTalkActiveName
eTalkActiveName.description: This is the EtherTalk name for the print server that is currently being used.

eTalkType1.name: eTalkType1
eTalkType1.description: Indicates the first EtherTalk type. This type is mandatory.

eTalkType2.name: eTalkType2
eTalkType2.description: Indicates the second EtherTalk type. This type is optional. Setting this name to NULL will disable it.

eTalkZone.name: eTalkZone
eTalkZone.description: Indicates the EtherTalk zone. This must be defined on the router.

eTalkActiveZone.name: eTalkActiveZone
eTalkActiveZone.description: Indicates the EtherTalk zone that is currently being used. This must be defined on the router.

eTalkError.name: eTalkError
eTalkError.description: Shows any errors for the EtherTalk protocol.

trapPrinterOnline.name: trapPrinterOnline
trapPrinterOnline.description: The printer is on-line. This trap will be sent out after a printer error condition has been cleared.

trapNoPrinterAttached.name: trapNoPrinterAttached
trapNoPrinterAttached.description: No printer is attached to the output port.

trapPrinterPaperOut.name: trapPrinterPaperOut
trapPrinterPaperOut.description: The printer is out of paper.

trapPrinterPaperJam.name: trapPrinterPaperJam
trapPrinterPaperJam.description: The printer has a paper jam.
